# Zyntel Security Rules

## PII (Healthcare)
- Never log PII: names, emails, phones, patient identifiers, hospital staff
- Form data validated server-side; never trust client
- Payment records immutable after creation — only status updates

## Headers
- CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options on all responses
- Rate limit auth and public endpoints

## Dependencies
- Run npm audit before merge
- Pin major versions; review updates for breaking changes

## Secrets
- No hardcoded keys, tokens, or passwords
- .env.example with placeholders only; never real values
